byline.original: By ELIZABETH A. HARRIS and COLIN MOYNIHAN

abstract: Hundred of demonstrators from the Occupy Wall Street movement march through streets of New York City in solidarity with protesters in Oakland, Calif, where police used tear gas to disperse crowds; about one dozen demonstrators are arrested.
snippet: Demonstrators wound through the financial district in a show of solidarity with those who clashed with the police in California on Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: Demonstrators wound through the financial district in a show of solidarity with those who clashed with the police in California on Tuesday.

headline.main: An Occupy Wall Street March to Support Those in Oakland
